Today it’s such an emotional day for me🤧😭… I’ve been crying since last night , watching countless videos and photos 😭- don’t judge me lol it’s my baby’s first day of school and as ready as I thought I would be for this day - the truth is that I wasn’t ! 😩 Rain has always been under my care or my mom’s daycare up until this day. So letting go fully and leaving him under the care of complete strangers for the first time hit me. 

Couldn’t help to overthink about a million things! Like  is he gonna be okay without us? Will he eat properly? Will they look out for him like we do ? And more !  But the one thing that left me a little bit more calm was seeing how much he has grown over the years and how independent he is with absolutely everything he does , sometimes he be making me feel like he doesn’t need me for anything 😭 lol .

I asked him this morning if he would cry when I leave it at school and he was like no Mami I’m not , why? And I was like -well I think mommy is gonna cry, and he laughed and said Mami don’t cry look at me I’m not crying , and I kid you not I broke down once again lol  but i cried because of how happy and proud of him I was for the way he was taking everything in and so mature at only 4 years old. 

I hope everyone has an amazing day and first day of school, kiss your baby’s and hug them tight every morning and remind them how much you love them ! 📚♥️ stay blessed and safe , love y’all ! 

#firstdayofschool #kindergarten #mommasboy💙 #iloveyou #myeverything #reels
